"title": "4488: oil",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4488: oil",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Normally olive oil, which was in plentiful supply in Israel and in general household use. Its ritual uses included the anointing of priests and kings and ceremonial cleansing; in the NT oil was used to anoint the sick. As a sign of God's provision for his people, oil was associated with prosperity and gladness, and was a mark of spiritual blessing.</p>\n<h2>The production of oil</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:11\">JOB 24:11</a> <em>Olives were pressed either with a pestle and mortar or in a stone press</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:36\">MAT 26:36</a> <em>“Gethsemane” means “oil press”, named after the stone presses associated with the Mount of Olives.</em></p>\n<h2>General uses of oil</h2>\n<h3>As a necessary provision</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:40\">1CH 12:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:11\">2CH 11:11</a></p>\n<h3>As a fuel for lamps</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:20\">EXO 27:20</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev24:2\">LEV 24:2</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:14\">EXO 35:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:37\">EXO 39:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:9\">NUM 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:1-Matt25:10\">MAT 25:1–25:10</a></p>\n<h3>Mixed with flour in baking</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:12-1Kgs17:16\">1KI 17:12–17:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:23\">EXO 29:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:8\">NUM 11:8</a></p>\n<h3>As an ointment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:6\">ISA 1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:21\">PSA 55:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:34\">LUK 10:34</a></p>\n<h2>Oil for use in the sanctuary</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:39\">NEH 10:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:6\">EXO 25:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:8\">EXO 35:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:16\">NUM 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:29\">1CH 9:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:9\">EZR 6:9</a></p>\n<h2>Oil used for ceremonial anointing</h2>\n<h3>Instructions for making and using the anointing oil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:23-Exod30:33\">EXO 30:23–30:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:11\">EXO 31:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod37:29\">EXO 37:29</a></p>\n<h3>Holy objects were consecrated by anointing with oil</h3>\n<p>Jacob twice anoints a pillar at Bethel:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:18\">GEN 28:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:13\">GEN 31:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:14\">GEN 35:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:9-Exod40:11\">EXO 40:9–40:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:10-Lev8:11\">LEV 8:10–8:11</a></p>\n<h3>Priests were ordained by anointing with oil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:12\">LEV 8:12</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:7\">EXO 29:7</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:21\">EXO 29:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:30\">LEV 8:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:7\">LEV 10:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:10-Lev21:12\">LEV 21:10–21:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps133:2\">PSA 133:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech4:12-Zech4:14\">ZEC 4:12–4:14</a></p>\n<h3>Kings were anointed with oil</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:1\">1SA 10:1</a> <em>Saul</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:20\">PSA 89:20</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:39\">1KI 1:39</a> <em>Solomon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:1-2Kgs9:6\">2KI 9:1–9:6</a> <em>Jehu</em></p>\n<h2>Further ceremonial uses of oil</h2>\n<h3>In ceremonial cleansing</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:15-Lev14:18\">LEV 14:15–14:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:24-Lev14:29\">LEV 14:24–14:29</a></p>\n<h3>In offerings</h3>\n<p>At the consecration of priests:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:2\">EXO 29:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:8\">NUM 8:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:40\">EXO 29:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:5\">NUM 28:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:1-Lev2:7\">LEV 2:1–2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:20-Lev6:21\">LEV 6:20–6:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:13\">NUM 7:13</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:12\">LEV 7:12</a> <em>with the thank offering</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:15\">NUM 6:15</a> <em>at the completion of the Nazirite's vow</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:9\">NUM 28:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:28\">NUM 28:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:4-Ezek46:5\">EZK 46:4–46:5</a></p>\n<h3>Oil was excluded from certain offerings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:11\">LEV 5:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:15\">NUM 5:15</a></p>\n<h2>Oil used to anoint the sick</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:14\">JAS 5:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:13\">MRK 6:13</a></p>\n<h2>God's provision of oil</h2>\n<h3>Oil as a sign of God's blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:13\">DEU 32:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:13\">DEU 7:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:7-Deut8:8\">DEU 8:7–8:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:14\">DEU 11:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:8\">HOS 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Oil withdrawn as a sign of judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:40\">DEU 28:40</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:51\">DEU 28:51</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:10\">JOL 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:15\">MIC 6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:11\">HAG 1:11</a></p>\n<h3>Renewed provision of oil following restoration</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:12\">JER 31:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:22\">HOS 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:18-Joel2:19\">JOL 2:18–2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:24\">JOL 2:24</a></p>\n<h3>The firstfruits of the oil harvest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:12\">NUM 18:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:4\">DEU 18:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:5\">2CH 31:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:37\">NEH 10:37</a></p>\n<h3>Tithes of oil</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:17\">DEU 12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:23\">DEU 14:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:12\">NEH 13:12</a></p>\n<h3>Oil as a commodity for trade</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:11\">1KI 5:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:10\">2CH 2:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:7\">EZR 3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:17\">EZK 27:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:1\">HOS 12:1</a></p>\n<h3>Oil as a sign of prosperity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:6\">JOB 29:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:24\">DEU 33:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:13\">2KI 20:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa39:2\">ISA 39:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:20\">PRO 21:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:9\">ISA 57:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:18-Ezek16:19\">EZK 16:18–16:19</a></p>\n<h3>Oil associated with celebration</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:7\">PSA 45:7</a></strong> <em>The joy with which God anoints his servants is likened to the oil which anoints the bridegroom in preparation for his wedding.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:15\">PSA 104:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:8\">ECC 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:3\">ISA 61:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:17\">MAT 6:17</a> <em>Oil draws attention away from the fact that a person is fasting</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:9\">HEB 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>Oil as a sign of honour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:5\">PSA 23:5</a></strong> <em>Oil was used to anoint the heads of honoured guests at a meal.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:5\">PSA 141:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:46\">LUK 7:46</a></p>",
